cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.MM, cs.LG 

This paper deals with channel estimation for massive MIMO systems using low-resolution ADCs. This topic falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science, including information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), signal processing (cs.SI), multimedia (cs.MM), and machine learning (cs.LG). Given the focus on signal processing and communication systems, cs.IT and cs.NI are the most likely categories. The use of statistical techniques and the exploitation of correlations in the channel suggest cs.SI as a possible category. The use of Kalman filters and the potential for machine learning techniques to improve channel estimation suggest cs.LG and cs.MM as additional possibilities.
